Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Hayes-style AT-command modem emulator bridging serial to TCP/Telnet
 modemu2k ships as a C library (libmodemu2k) exposing the modem state
 machine, plus a small CLI built on top. The CLI allocates a PTY and
 either reads stdin/stdout directly, forks a comm program (minicom,
 picocom) on the slave, or accepts an incoming TCP connection as the
 TTY. IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.
 .
 modemu2k is a fork of modemu, originally developed by Toru Egashira.
